The defendant Timothy G Harring was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Timothy G Harring is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

Defendant Timothy G Harring in court with attorney Amanda K Riek.  Jordan Lippert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Waiver of Preliminary Hearing filed. Court found probable cause, bound defendant over. Information filed, reading waived. Court went over the rights & elements. Defendant plead no contest to count one. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment, sentence withheld, 2 yrs. probation, conds: $268 costs, $250 DNA surcharge, submit DNA sample, it not previously provided. Complete AODA assessment, follow all treatment recommendations, periodic review in six months.  No jail credit. Ct. 2 dismissed.
